    <category>News</category>
    <guid>http://www.costain.com/news/news-releases/2013/2/13/innovation-award-for-costain-manager.aspx</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<p>13 February 2013</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Costain Manager, James Bulleid has capped a remarkable year by winning the New Engineering Foundation (NEF) Innovator of the Year Award.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Innovation Awards were presented at the NEF’s annual ‘Innovisions’ conference at the Institute of Directors in London. They were established last year to recognise and celebrate the best in UK innovation. </p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Winners of the eight categories were decided by a panel of industry experts, opinion-formers and leaders including the award sponsors EMC, BASF and National Grid.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">“The winners were chosen due to their clarity of intended purpose, uniqueness of approach, potential impact, and whether they stimulated and galvanised others,” said Professor Sa’ad Medhat, CEO of the NEF.  “The winners will contribute to a culture of innovation which will help promote sustainable growth in the UK.”</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">James joined Costain as a Graduate Engineer. The main factor behind his accolade was recognition of an overall mindset towards innovation and technology-led solutions.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">“The NEF was interested in how I transferred a series of technical solutions into a construction environment, bringing together two industries that don’t often merge,” he commented.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">He was put forward for the award by Group Innovation Manager, Tim Embley. It was the latest in a series of prizes in 2012, including Trainee of the Year at the Company’s Achieving Excellence Awards, one of the Sir Albert Costain Memorial Awards, as well as Construction News’s Rising Star of the Year Award.  He also achieved Chartered status in civil engineering.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">He is currently Mobilisation Manager for a highway technology maintenance contract. His role also includes strategy and business development for Costain’s Highways sector.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Ends</p>]]></description>
    
</item>

<item>
    <title><![CDATA[Top Marks For Brighton And Hove]]></title>
    <link>http://www.costain.com/news/news-releases/2013/2/12/top-marks-for-brighton-and-hove.aspx</link>                        
    <pubDate>Tue, 12 Feb 2013 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    <dc:creator></dc:creator>
    <category>News</category>
    <guid>http://www.costain.com/news/news-releases/2013/2/12/top-marks-for-brighton-and-hove.aspx</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<p>12 February 2013</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Costain joint venture team (4Delivery) behind Southern Water’s Cleaner Seas for Sussex Peacehaven Wastewater Treatment Works has achieved a remarkable performance in the Considerate Constructors Scheme (CCS).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">A monitor’s report in late January gave the site, which is hugely improving the quality of wastewater treatment from the Brighton and Hove catchment area, a rating of 47 out of 50.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Three of the categories measured – ‘Enhancing the site’s appearance’, ‘Protecting the environment’ and ‘Securing everyone’s safety’ – were marked as 9/10, or ‘exceptional’, while ‘Respecting the community’ and ‘Caring for the workforce’ scored a full 10.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This latter score is only awarded where performance is deemed ‘Innovative’ and setting new standards that can be incorporated into the CCS for future projects.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">In the case of ‘Respecting the community’, that has entailed huge efforts over the years to keep  local residents on-side for what had been regarded for many years before construction got underway as a controversial project.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">There have been 2,000 site visitors over the construction phase and two educational videos have been made for local residents, one showing the progress of wastewater from the time someone flushes their toilet to the moment when the treated wastewater is released to sea, the other explaining the tunnelling required to construct the long sea outfall.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The team’s achievement is all the more impressive given changes in the CCS scoring system, which makes gaining a high mark even more challenging, said Senior Project Manager, Graham Sugrue. “It’s a lot more difficult now. It’s based on innovation and going the extra mile; it’s about doing more than the norm.  Everyone has put in a huge effort; the CCS score reflects this.”</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The project is nearing completion, with commissioning well underway.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Ends</p>]]></description>
    
</item>

<item>
    <title><![CDATA[Showcase For Graduates And Apprentices]]></title>
    <link>http://www.costain.com/news/news-releases/2013/2/11/showcase-for-graduates-and-apprentices.aspx</link>                        
    <pubDate>Mon, 11 Feb 2013 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    <dc:creator></dc:creator>
    <category>News</category>
    <guid>http://www.costain.com/news/news-releases/2013/2/11/showcase-for-graduates-and-apprentices.aspx</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">11 February 2013</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Costain is showcasing its range of vocational opportunities for graduates and apprentices at the upcoming Heathrow Jobs &amp; Careers Fair.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The event, which is scheduled to take place on February 12 at the Renaissance London Heathrow Hotel from 9.30am to 7pm, is free to enter and aims to encourage the 320 companies that work at London’s Heathrow Airport to recruit local people from the Ealing, Hillingdon, Hounslow, Slough and Spelthorne area.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The fair gives visitors, whether they’re students, teachers or parents, an opportunity to meet prospective employers and to get a better understanding about the range of opportunities available for school leavers and graduates.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The airport employs a large and diverse workforce in areas such as airline staff, security personnel, ground crew, fire and police officers, engineers, construction workers, caterers and retail staff, and all of the companies that work at Heathrow in these sectors will be represented at the event.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Costain has worked on a number of projects at Heathrow, which is one of the world’s busiest international airports with over 190,000 passengers a day across five terminals, including the repair and maintenance of existing infrastructure.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">“The Heathrow Jobs &amp; Careers Fair gives employers like Costain a fantastic opportunity to inform prospective apprentices and graduate trainees what skills, qualifications and characteristics we are looking for so they can make an informed decision about what career path to take and how Costain can help them,” said Joe Kemm, Costain’s Operations Director Airports.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Investing in young people and helping the industry address a long-term skills shortage is an integral component of Costain Cares, the Group’s strategy to build a long-term sustainable business. Now in its third year, the Costain Apprentice Scheme delivers training and employment opportunities to young people seeking a career in the construction and civil engineering industry and in fields ranging from engineering construction to business administration.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Donna Rose will be hosting Costain’s stand and giving prospective candidates the information they need about a career within the Group.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">“Costain offers a wealth of opportunity for school leavers and graduates looking for a career in the construction and engineering industry. We’ll be giving advice about career progression and, if they’re interested, what the next steps are,” said Donna.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">For more information or to pre-register to attend, visit</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.heathrowjobsandcareersfair.co.uk/">www.heathrowjobsandcareersfair.co.uk</a> or </p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/HeathrowJobsCareersFair">http://www.facebook.com/HeathrowJobsCareersFair</a> or call 01823 362800.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Ends</p>]]></description>
    
</item>

<item>
    <title><![CDATA[Excellence Recognised At Costain Awards ]]></title>
    <link>http://www.costain.com/news/news-releases/2013/2/8/excellence-recognised-at-costain-awards.aspx</link>                        
    <pubDate>Fri, 08 Feb 2013 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    <dc:creator></dc:creator>
    <category>News</category>
    <guid>http://www.costain.com/news/news-releases/2013/2/8/excellence-recognised-at-costain-awards.aspx</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">8 February 2013</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Costain celebrated last night the achievements and outstanding performance of its people from across the Group at its Achieving Excellence Awards 2012.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Held at Norden Farm Centre for the Arts in Maidenhead, the event was hosted by Jonathan Stebbings from Olivier Mythodrama, a company which specialises in using the works of Shakespeare to highlight the qualities of leadership. Attendees heard how, through exceptional performance, Costain’s employees galvanised those around them and enhanced the Company’s reputation for operational excellence.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This year, a special award, Costain’s Brand Award, was given to the Bond Street Team (Crossrail) C411 for its work in enhancing the Costain brand while working on Europe’s biggest rail infrastructure project. This complex project also happens to be in the heart of the UK’s busiest shopping district and the team was applauded for its community engagement, dedication and high level of customer service.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Chief Executive, Andrew Wyllie, said: “We are delighted to be recognising the outstanding performances of individuals and teams with these Costain Achieving Excellence Awards 2012. We are Meeting National Needs by engineering excellence in every facet of our operations.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">"These Awards graphically illustrate that we achieve just that. In total, we received 1,300 nominations from Costain people, highlighting the efforts and achievements of skilled individuals at all levels in the Company. In terms of innovation, our people have developed new ways of operating which have saved time, increased profit and improved performance.  In the area of safety, our efforts continue to reduce accidents and ensure that people go home from work safe and sound. Other categories showcase similar successes. This Company is extremely proud of its people and these Awards demonstrate why. Costain would not exist without its people and would not be such a respected brand without the type of outstanding performance which we now have a chance to applaud.”</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The winners and the shortlisted nominees for each award are listed below.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>Contribution to Safety</strong></em></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Shortlisted Nominees</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Alan Cheung<br />Simon Cooper<br />Simon Cox<br />Fiddlers Ferry Site Team – Mechanical Services<br />Gary Hill<br />Joseph Kemm</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Winner:</strong><br />Fiddlers Ferry Site Team – Mechanical Services<br />• Six years without accident<br />• 24/7 operation<br />• Customer satisfaction</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>Business Development / Customer Satisfaction</strong></em></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Shortlisted Nominees</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Andrew Beedle<br />Chris Scott<br />Graham Callander<br />Highways Team<br />James Bulleid<br />Matt Crabtree</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Winner:</strong><br />Chris Scott<br />• Helping to drive operations and maintenance throughout the Group<br />• Major role in securing Magnox contract<br />• Personal drive</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>Unsung Hero</strong></em></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Shortlisted Nominees</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">David Forbes<br />Carol Harle<br />Sandeep Mashiana<br />Diane Miller<br />Alistair Procter<br />Chris Raine</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Winner:</strong><br />Diane Miller<br />• Excellent service over 25 years<br />• Extremely conscientious<br />• A highly valued team member</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>Trainee of the Year</strong></em></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Shortlisted Nominees</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Claire Baker<br />Luke Fisher<br />James Hawkes<br />Shingai Musonza<br />Muneeb Nawaz<br />Ros Parker<br />Sophie Tuckett<br />Mahsa Zargary</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Winner:</strong><br />Claire Baker<br />• Major role in delivering climate change programme<br />• Key member of Health and Safety<br />• High number of nominations</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><em><strong>Innovation of the Year</strong></em></p>
