    <description><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">17 January 2013</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Richard Brownson, Costain General Foreman on the Dwr Cymru Welsh Water Framework, is a local hero after helping to rescue a lorry driver who was trapped in his overturned cab.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Following an accident on the A55 in North Wales, Richard noticed a cloud of white smoke and immediately pulled over to assist. He could see a man trapped in the back of his meat lorry and instinctively tried to free him from the wreckage.</p>
