    <guid>http://www.costain.com/news/news-releases/2012/5/23/costain-signs-up-to-new-safety-agreement.aspx</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;">23 May 2012</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Costain has signed up to a health and safety accord designed to set standards for the offshore wind and marine energy sector.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The agreement was signed for Costain by Chief Executive, Andrew Wyllie, and on behalf of Gravitas Offshore, the consortium comprising Costain, Hochtief and Arup, by Managing Director, Environment, Alan Kay.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Alan is a Director of Gravitas Offshore, which is proposing a concrete flask-shaped structure that sits on the seabed as a base for offshore wind turbines.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Costain is one of the first construction industry participants to put its name to the accord, which is sponsored by RenewableUK, the trade association for the sector: “We’re signing up to demonstrate our commitment to and support for health and safety excellence in the offshore renewables sector,” said Director of Renewables, Colin Duff.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The accord was drawn up by RenewableUK and is the result of active engagement with key stakeholders including the Health &amp; Safety Executive and The Crown Estate, which owns the seabed inside UK territorial waters.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Meanwhile, Colin reports good progress with Gravitas Offshore, with its base design having aroused considerable interest in the offshore energy industry.</p>
