<p>Hewlett, an ICE member since 1990 and a Fellow for the past three years, will serve a three-year term as vice-president for membership and ethics.</p>
<p>The role includes chairing the membership panel that maintains the infrastructure supporting people aiming to join the institution and reviews their applications. It also aims to ensure that the need for ethical behaviour in the job is understood.</p>
