<p>18 October 2010</p>

<p>Costain announces that it has been awarded a contract from
National Grid for its London Cable Replacement Tunnel.</p>

<p>The contract is worth approximately £200 million and forms part
of National Grid's investment plans in the capital to ensure a
continued safe and reliable electricity transmission network.</p>

<p>The contract is to build a new high voltage electricity cable
tunnel between Hackney and Willesden (via Kensal Green) and Kensal
Green and Wimbledon. The tunnel is a total of 33km long.</p>

