    <description><![CDATA[
<p>28 September 2010</p>

<p>Costain's growing strength in mobile technology has been
acknowledged by an industry body charged with promoting the use of
the technology.</p>

<p>Construction Opportunities for Mobile IT (COMIT) has awarded
Costain its 2010 Commitment to Innovation award for its efforts in
applying mobile technology to improve efficiency and save costs on
its projects.</p>

<p>The award acknowledges Costain's position in the vanguard of the
construction industry in adopting mobile technology.</p>

<p>Among the Company's initiatives have been the use of Radio
Frequency Identification tags to track plant and equipment and
using electronic signatures on personal data assistants that allow
engineers to sign off satisfactorily completed sections of work,
rather than using paper documents. And vehicle-mounted equipment
incorporating a Global Positioning System is being used to carry
out topographic surveys of large areas faster and more safely than
the traditional method of someone working on foot.</p>

<p>COMIT consists of some 60-plus construction companies and
technology providers. It aims to promote the use of mobile
technology within the UK construction sector by spreading best
practice, promoting new developments and improving understanding
between both groups.</p>

<p>Companies such as Costain can detail technological problems they
face in their work and seek solutions from equipment vendor COMIT
members, explains Aalok Sonawala, Business Improvement and Systems
Manager on the Brighton and Hove wastewater treatment works
project, who received the COMIT award.</p>

<ul>
<li>Costain's progress in this field was detailed in website
article <em>Intelligent phones</em> on 22 September.</li>
</ul>

