    <dc:creator></dc:creator>
    <category>News</category>
    <guid>http://www.costain.com/news/news-releases/2010/9/1/adgas-contract-awarded-to-costain-abu-dhabi.aspx</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[
<p>1 September 2010</p>

<p>Costain Abu Dhabi Company W.L.L has been recently awarded a
contract by Abu Dhabi Gas Liquefaction Company Limited
(ADGAS).&nbsp;</p>

<p>The contract's scope comprises procurement, construction and
commissioning of the Flare Handling Emission Reduction (FHER)
project which will reduce flaring and emissions from the existing
LNG plant on Das Island.</p>

<p>ADGAS is implementing the recovery and utilization of waste gas
currently flared in the gas refinery complex.&nbsp; The waste gases
will be recovered from Train 1, 2 and 3 of the plant and will be
fed to the pipeline between the booster compressor (BC) and feed
gas compressor (FGC).&nbsp;</p>

<p>The recovery and utilization of waste gases will reduce the
natural gas consumption in the plant and save greenhouse gas (GHG)
emissions.&nbsp; The project is first of its kind in the UAE and is
being submitted to the United Nations under the Clean Development
Mechanism (CDM).</p>

<p>The project is scheduled to be completed within&nbsp;nine
months.</p>

<p>Alastair Smith, General Manager, commented: "The award of this
project from ADGAS is significant and gives us an opportunity to
build a further relationship with our clients by delivering high
quality and improved performance on our projects".</p>

<p><br />
Ends</p>
]]></description>
    
</item>

